{
  "texts": [
    "In essence, we use LLMs to automate the process of identifying different lifestyle items.",
    "To prepare for work with LLMs and to be able to calibrate and evaluate the performance of the model, researchers should select and analyze a subset of data by hand.",
    "To retrieve the correct lifestyle-related word(s), we randomly select 100 Twitter self-descriptions and manually code them to make a codebook foot_3 that guides the LLM.",
    "This selection is also referred to as holdout data.",
    "Holdout data, also known as validation data or test data, is one of the standard practices for reliably evaluating machine learning models (Dwork et al., 2015)."
  ]
}